body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Consider the following piece of code:

```
module top  (y, clk, wire3, wire2);
  output wire [(32'h50):(32'h0)] y;
  input wire [(1'h0):(1'h0)] clk;
  input wire signed [(5'h15):(1'h0)] wire3;
  input wire signed [(2'h3):(1'h0)] wire2;
  reg signed [(5'h15):(1'h0)] reg10 = (1'h0);
  assign y = {reg10};
  always
    @(posedge clk) reg10 <= (-$signed((-(wire2 << {wire3}))));
endmodule
```

Run with yosys version

       Generated by Yosys 0.9+4081 (git sha1 UNKNOWN, clang 10.0.0-4ubuntu1 -fPIC -Os)

and the following command

     yosys -p 'read_verilog  rtl.v; synth; write_verilog  syn_yosys.v'

## Expected behavior

    when Executing CHECK pass and Verilog backend,get a corresponding Write Design to Verilog file

## Actual behavior

    The corresponding Verilog file is an empty function
 `/* Generated by Yosys 0.9+4081 (git sha1 UNKNOWN, clang 10.0.0-4ubuntu1 -fPIC -Os) */

module \$abstract\top ();
endmodule`


We think this should be a bug.

